        Creates an account.

        Target API Endpoint: /account/create
        Parameters:
        name - The full name of the user. If this parameter is not empty, the following parameters will be ignored: prefixName, firstName, middleName, lastName, and suffixName
        prefixName - if the parameter 'name' is empty or not present, this field will be used to set the prefix of the user's name
        firstName - if the parameter 'name' is empty or not present, this field will be used to set the user's first name
        middleName - if the parameter 'name' is empty or not present, this field will be used to set the user's middle name
        lastName - if the parameter 'name' is empty or not present, this field will be used to set the user's last name
        suffixName - if the parameter 'name' is empty or not present, this field will be used to set the suffix of the user's name
        title - this field will be used to set the user's job title
        username - the encrypted email of the user, this is what will be used when they login
        password - the encrypted password of the user
        assetId - the asset id to set the user's profile image
        streetAddress - the street address of the user's contact location
        zipcode - the street zipcode of the user's contact location
        gender - the gender
        birthday - the birthday
        homePhone - the home phone
        cellPhone - the cell phone
        cellPhoneCarrier - the cell phone carrier
        businessPhone - the business phone
        role - the type of account being created {RETAILER, MEMBER, DEVELOPER, GUEST}
        platforms - list of development platforms {MAC, WINDOWS, IOS, ANDROID, WINDOWSPHONE, KINDLE, UNITY3D, COCOS2D, HTML5, FACEBOOK}
        tags - list of search tags
        gameExperience - game experience level of the user {ANY, NEW, BEGINNER, INTERMEDIATE, EXPERT}
        hometown - the user's hometown
        height - the user's height
        heightIndex - the user's height in a numerical value that can be used for ordering/searching
        ethnicity - the user's ethnicity
        bodyType - the user's body type
        maritalStatus - the user's maritial status
        children - the user's children status
        religion - the user's religion
        education - the user's education
        educationIndex - the user's education in a numerical value that can be used for ordering/searching
        smoke - the user's smoke status
        drink - the user's drink status
        companionship - the user's companionship status
        companionshipIndex - the user's companionship index
        preferredMinAge - the preferred minimum age in the account location search
        preferredMaxAge - the preferred maximum age in the account location search
        preferredMinHeight - the preferred minimum height in the account location search
        preferredMaxHeight - the preferred maximum height in the account location search
        preferredGender - the preferred gender in the account location search
        preferredEducation - the preferred education in the account location search
        preferredEducationIndex - the preferred education in a numerical value that can be used for ordering/searching
        preferredBodyType - the preferred body type in the account location search
        preferredEthnicity - the preferred ethnicity in the account location search
        preferredLocation - the preferred education in the account location search
        preferredLocationRange - the preferred location range in the account location search
        location - the current location of the user
        acceptedTerms - if the user has accepted the terms of service
        appKey - the application key. A unique id of the app. Maps to "gameType".
        appVersion - the version of the application. AppVersion
        responseType - the response type, use "AccountResponse" for AccountLoginResponse. Otherwise, SirqulResponse.
        Returns:
        the AccountLoginResponse
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

      • getAccount

        public SirqulResponse getAccount(String username,
                        String password,
                        Location location,
                        String appKey,
                        Boolean returnProfile,
                        List<Enums.ProfileFilters> responseFilters)
                          throws SirqulException
        Gets the account.

        Target API Endpoint: /account/get
        Parameters:
        username - the user's email address they used to sign-up
        password - the password
        location - the current location of the user
        appKey - the application key for which the user is logging in to. Maps to "gameType" in call.
        returnProfile - determines whether to return a ProfileResponse on success, or a PaymentTypesResponse. Default is false.
        responseFilters - if returnProfile is set to true, this determines how much of the profile should be returned, see Enums.ProfileFilters
        Returns:
        if returnProfile is true, a ProfileResponse on valid response, else if false, a PaymentTypesResponse on valid response, or SirqulResponse on an invalid response with error message
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

      • searchConnectionsByRangeAndName

        public UserLocationSearchResponse searchConnectionsByRangeAndName(Long accountId,
                                                         List<Enums.ConnectionApiMap> filters,
                                                         String keyword,
                                                         String postalCode,
                                                         Location location,
                                                         Double range,
                                                         Long locationLastUpdated,
                                                         Enums.AudienceGender gender,
                                                         Integer minimumAge,
                                                         Integer maximumAge,
                                                         Integer companionshipIndex,
                                                         Integer start,
                                                         Integer limit,
                                                         String appKey,
                                                         Boolean updateCurrentLocation,
                                                         Boolean updatePreferredSettings)
                                                           throws SirqulException
        Search accounts by their location. This only searches on users that have location data. Use searchConnectionsByName to perform a regular search on accounts.

        Target API Endpoint: /account/search
        Parameters:
        accountId - the account id of the user (deviceId or accountId required)
        filters - list of Enums.ConnectionApiMap, to filter results
        keyword - an optional keyword to search on, will be ignore if empty (NOT implemented yet)
        postalCode - the postal code to search on, either postalCode or the user's exact location is required
        location - the location of the user, either postalCode or the user's exact location is required
        range - the range to search on
        locationLastUpdated - searches for user's that has updated their location since this date
        gender - the preferred gender
        minimumAge - the preferred min age
        maximumAge - the preferred max age
        companionshipIndex - the preferred companionship index
        start - the start index of the pagination
        limit - the limit of the pagination
        appKey - the application key. Maps to "gameType".
        updateCurrentLocation - whether to use the given lat & long to update the user's current location
        updatePreferredSettings - whether to use the given parameters to update the user's preferred settings
        Returns:
        a UserLocationSearchResponse on valid response, or SirqulResponse with error message
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

        suffixName - if the parameter 'name' is empty or not present, this field will be used to set the suffix of the user's name
        title - the title
        username - the encrypted email of the user, this is what will be used when they login
        password - the encrypted password of the user
        assetId - the asset id to set the user's profile image
        address - the address
        zipcode - the street zipcode of the user's contact location
        gender - the gender of the user Enums.AudienceGender
        birthday - the birthday date of the user in milliseconds
        homePhone - the home phone
        cellPhone - the cell phone
        cellPhoneCarrier - the cell phone carrier
        businessPhone - the business phone
        role - the type of account being created {RETAILER, MEMBER, DEVELOPER, GUEST}
        platforms - comma separated list of development platforms {MAC, WINDOWS, IOS, ANDROID, WINDOWSPHONE, KINDLE, UNITY3D, COCOS2D, HTML5, FACEBOOK}
        tags - search tags
        gameExperience - game experience level of the user {ANY, NEW, BEGINNER, INTERMEDIATE, EXPERT}
        hometown - the user's hometown
        height - the user's height
        heightIndex - the user's height in a numerical value that can be used for ordering/searching
        ethnicity - the user's ethnicity
        bodyType - the user's body type
        maritalStatus - the user's maritial status
        children - the user's children status
        religion - the user's religion
        education - the user's education
        educationIndex - the user's education in a numerical value that can be used for ordering/searching
        smoke - the user's smoke status
        drink - the user's drink status
        companionship - the user's companionship status
        companionshipIndex - the user's companionship index
        preferredMinAge - the preferred minimum age in the account location search
        preferredMaxAge - the preferred maximum age in the account location search
        preferredMinHeight - the preferred minimum height in the account location search
        preferredMaxHeight - the preferred maximum height in the account location search
        preferredGender - the preferred gender in the account location search
        preferredEducation - the preferred education in the account location search
        preferredEducationIndex - the preferred education in a numerical value that can be used for ordering/searching
        preferredBodyType - the preferred body type in the account location search
        preferredEthnicity - the preferred ethnicity in the account location search
        preferredLocation - the preferred education in the account location search
        preferredLocationRange - the preferred location range in the account location search
        location - the location of the user
        acceptedTerms - the accepted terms
        appKey - the app key
        appVersion - the app version
        responseType - the response type
        Returns:
        ProfileInfoResponse on a valid response, SirqulResponse on an invalid response
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.
